President Trump welcomed America's sheriffs to the White House and expressed his support for law enforcement officers. He mentioned that his administration has provided military equipment to help them in their work and encouraged them to continue doing their job well. Trump highlighted the efforts to combat gun crimes, drug dealers, and drug pushers as the number one way to stop drugs. He called on Congress to support his immigration policy to keep out terrorists, drug dealers, criminals, and gang members. He also mentioned that they are working on DACA and immigration bills to strengthen immigration laws. Trump emphasized that securing the border, ending chain migration, and canceling the visa lottery are vital elements of a safe immigration system. He reiterated that the safety and security of the American people are a priority and thanked the sheriffs for their presence.